Thunderstorm warning: The NWS has issued the following warning: The National Weather Service in San Diego issued a Severe Thunderstorm Warning for Western San Diego County until 6:45 PM PST. 
The National Weather Service identified a line of severe thunderstorms capable of producing damaging winds in excess of 60 mph. This intense line of heavy rain and high wind will move into coastal cities between 6:00 and 6:30 pm.
Locations impacted include Chula Vista, Oceanside, Carlsbad, El Cajon, Vista, Encinitas, National City, La Mesa, Poway, North Park, Point Loma, Hillcrest, Midway District Including Lindbergh Field, Downtown San Diego and La Jolla.

Signs of potential autism spectrum disorder can be detected in high-risk infants as young as 12 months with 80 percent accuracy, according to an international study published Wednesday.

The study used MRI brains scans to provide the earliest physical evidence of autism-associated brain abnormalities in high-risk infants, defined as those who have at least one older sibling with autism. It supports other research suggesting that overgrowth of certain brain regions is involved in autism.
link_name: Autism signs may be detectable at 12 months, study says

status_message: Lightning alert: We've had reports of thunder in downtown San Diego and Mt. Helix. The NWS says that thunder and lightning can occur anywhere in the county today. The storm has a lot of cold, unstable air that's conducive to convection. Hikingdude.com says that if you're caught outside in a lightning storm, you should " become a small, round target and cross your fingers. Minimize your contact with the ground and minimize your height. Crouching down on the balls of your feet placed close together with your head tucked down is the recommended position."  (Image taken in December in Gaza City by Getty.)

status_message:
AMBER ALERT: An amber alert has been issued across California for a 1-year-old boy from San Pedro in Los Angeles. Jayden Nathaniel Santiago is believed to be with his father, 37-year-old Giovany Santiago-Enriquez. Santiago-Enriquez is suspected of going to his ex-girlfriend's home and stabbing her and her boyfriend early this morning. Police believe he is armed and dangerous, as well as, suicidal. Santiago-Enriquez drives a 2006 gray Nissan Altima with California license plate 5UCF010. He may be headed to Washington state and/or Mexico, authorities said.

If you see Santiago-Enriquez and/or Jayden, please contact the Los Angeles Police Department, Harbor Division at (310) 726-7700 or 911. #AmberAlert

status_message: In June 2007,a Rancho Bernardo dentist was placed on probation by the state dental board for five years after a series of incidents, including one in which a patient's face caught fire. A week after he was put on probation — but allowed to go on practicing — a 15-year-old Ramona boy died of heart failure while sedated during oral surgery in his care.
link_name: 'Face on fire' dentist went on practicing

status_message: When the San Diego-Coronado Bridge opened Aug. 3, 1969, it became an instant landmark. The bridge ascends at a 4.67 percent grade from Coronado before curving 90 degrees toward San Diego. The curve makes the span long enough so it can rise to a height of 200 feet, allowing even the Navy's tallest ships to sail under. It also forever changed Coronado.
